# Implementation Standards

- Write code that is obvious to maintainers; avoid hidden control flow.
- Co-locate related logic and keep module boundaries intentional.
- Prefer pure functions and dependency injection where practical.
- Handle errors explicitly with actionable messages and consistent strategy.
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions; extract only when reuse or clarity justifies it.
- Keep naming domain-driven: business language over technical noise.
- Add brief comments only for non-obvious decisions or invariants.
